# Build output — installers and Pi packages. `*.exe` was already covered; these were not,
# and a 32 MB pi-out/Nexus_*_arm64.deb was one `git add -A` away from being permanent.
pi-out/
*.deb
*.AppImage

# Internal planning notes live in the PRIVATE kd9taw/nexus-notes repo and are cloned
# here for convenience. They are deliberately NOT part of the published source.
#
# They used to be tracked here and removed from every publish by a manual scrub. That
# scrub is what let a stale hand-merged libtempo/CMakeLists.txt ship source that could
# not compile for two releases (2026-07-20). Keeping notes out of this repo means the
# published tree IS the tree that gets built and tested — nothing to strip, no drift.
tasks/
# ops/ = internal runbooks (hosting, data-refresh cadences). Same rule as tasks/: kept
# on disk for convenience, never published (they name the private hamtoolssite checkout).
ops/
